Late closings

   The Fondation Cartier is exceptionally open for an additional
   late-closing night on Thursday evenings until 10 pm.

   Book a priority-access ticket

   Exhibition in Paris

Trees .

   From July 12 to November 10, 2019

   Late closing on Tuesday and Thursday, at 10 pm
   Book a ticket

   Bringing together a community of artists, botanists, and philosophers,
   the Fondation Cartier pour l’art contemporain echoes the latest
   scientific research that sheds new light on trees. Organized around
   several large ensembles of works, the exhibition Trees gives voice to
   numerous figures who, through their...
   Read more

   View of the exhibition Trees, Fondation Cartier pour l’art
   contemporain, Paris, 2019. © Francis Hallé. Picture © Luc Boegly.

   View of the exhibition Trees, Fondation Cartier pour l’art
   contemporain, Paris, 2019. © Johanna Calle. Picture © Luc Boegly.

   View of the exhibition Trees, Fondation Cartier pour l’art
   contemporain, Paris, 2019. © Cesare Leonardi, Franca Stagi. Picture ©
   Luc Boegly.

   View of the exhibition Trees, Fondation Cartier pour l’art
   contemporain, Paris, 2019. © Stefano Mancuso. Picture © Luc Boegly.

   View of the exhibition Trees, Fondation Cartier pour l’art
   contemporain, Paris, 2019. © Fabrice Hyber. Picture © Luc Boegly.

   View of the exhibition Trees, Fondation Cartier pour l’art
   contemporain, Paris, 2019. © Luiz Zerbini. Picture © Luc Boegly.

   View of the exhibition Trees, Fondation Cartier pour l’art
   contemporain, Paris, 2019. © Paz Encina. Picture © Luc Boegly.

   View of the exhibition Trees, Fondation Cartier pour l’art
   contemporain, Paris, 2019. © Luiz Zerbini. Picture © Luc Boegly.

   View of the exhibition Trees, Fondation Cartier pour l’art
   contemporain, Paris, 2019. © Luiz Zerbini. Picture © Luc Boegly.

   The exhibition debunks the idea that humans are masters of creation,
   arguing that plants are not “less” – just radically different. A
   mind-bending trip to the forest

     Simon Ings, Financial Times

