Fondation Cartier and Triennale Milano announce groundbreaking cultural
partnership

   The Fondation Cartier pour l’art contemporain and Triennale Milano are
   pleased to announce their collaboration. Together, they will present in
   Milan, in the exhibition spaces of the Italian institution, a program
   of exhibitions and live performances from April 2020 onwards.

   This collaboration will be inaugurated with the presentation of the
   Fondation Cartier collection, curated by Argentinian artist Guillermo
   Kuitca. It will continue in fall 2020 with the exhibition Claudia
   Andujar, The Yanomami Struggle, devoted to the remarkable work of this
   Brazilian artist.

   Triennale Milano, Milan. Photo © Gianluca Di Ioia

   Picture © Yunling Fang.

